{"type":"message","id":"3a54bba4","parentId":"3a2446de","timestamp":"2026-06-10T10:52:48.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"strings utility is not available on Windows. Let me use PowerShell's approach or find another way. Actually, I can use `Select-String` natively on the binary file but it's very large (81MB). Let me try a more targeted approach - I'll read hex strings from the binary using .NET.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nbJa8lG595NWydokemSe1252","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use PowerShell to extract readable strings from the libil2cpp.so and search for login/API patterns\n$path = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\lib\\arm64-v8a\\libil2cpp.so\"\n$fs = [System.IO.File]::OpenRead($path)\n$buffer = New-Object byte[] 10485760  # 10MB buffer\n$bytesRead = $fs.Read($buffer, 0, $buffer.Length)\n$fs.Close()\n\n# Extract ASCII strings (4+ chars)\n$sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder\n$strings = @()\n$minLen = 6\n$currentLen = 0\n\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $bytesRead; $i++) {\n    $b = $buffer[$i]\n    if ($b -ge 32 -and $b -le 126) {\n        $sb.Append([char]$b) | Out-Null\n        $currentLen++\n    } else {\n        if ($currentLen -ge $minLen) {\n            $strings += $sb.ToString()\n        }\n        $sb.Clear()\n        $currentLen = 0\n    }\n}\n\n# Filter for login/API related strings\n$loginRelated = $strings | Where-Object { \n    $_ -match \"login|auth|token|foxwq|yhwq|passwd|password|sdk|api\" \n}\n\n$loginRelated | Sort-Object -Unique | Select-Object -First 80","timeout":120,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":176,"output":466,"cacheRead":56064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56706,"cost":{"input":0.00002464,"output":0.00013048,"cacheRead":0.001569792,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0017249119999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781088763349,"responseId":"1eba63d8-b035