{"type":"message","id":"dd0ff456","parentId":"b6796c71","timestamp":"2026-06-10T10:53:56.818Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The binary reading is still running. It's taking too long and producing a lot of garbage. Let me kill it and try a different, more efficient approach. Instead of reading 10MB of the 81MB binary and trying to extract strings in PowerShell (which is clearly very slow), let me try using C# or a better approach.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. The login flow is:\n1. User taps \"微信登录/QQ登录/谷歌登录\" in Unity UI\n2. Unity calls to Java bridge (via UnityPlayer.UnitySendMessage or similar)\n3. Java side uses the respective SDK (WeChat/QQ/Google) to get OAuth tokens\n4. Java calls back to Unity with the token/user data\n5. Unity then calls its own backend API to authenticate with the third-party token\n\nSo the actual game backend login API call is in the Unity C# code (compiled to IL2CPP). To extract meaningful strings from an 81MB binary is going to take a long time via PowerShell.\n\nLet me try a more focused approach - search for specific patterns using Select-String on the binary file directly, but only for obvious URL patterns.\n\nActually, let me check the Assets files - those are likely the Unity resource bundle files that might contain config data.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QBRJ4vpIi96r477XXFJM7832","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if any asset files contain readable login-related strings\n$assetsDir = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\assets\"\n# Look for config files, txt files, xml, json\nGet-ChildItem $assetsDir -Recurse -Include \"*.txt\", \"*.xml\", \"*.json\", \"*.bytes\", \"*.csv\", \"*.yaml\" | Select-Object FullName, Length\n\nWrite-Host \"=== Check bin/Data for config files ===\"\nGet-ChildItem \"$assetsDir\\bin\\Data\" -File | Select-Object Name, Length | Sort-Object Name","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":11416,"output":460,"cacheRead":56832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68708,"cost":{"input":0.0015982400000000001,"output":0.00012880000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0015912959999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003318336}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781088830152,"responseId":"10b0f660-78ad-4a99-b2b9-32bac428a9bf"}}
