{"type":"message","id":"528cd406","parentId":"382c57c4","timestamp":"2026-06-10T10:54:07.564Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key assemblies are:\n- Assembly-CSharp-firstpass.dll (type 16)\n- Assembly-CSharp.dll (type 16)\n\nThese are the main game code DLLs. Since this is IL2CPP, these DLLs are compiled into libil2cpp.so. The type \"16\" means they're part of the compiled code.\n\nLet me try a more efficient approach with the binary. Instead of reading the whole thing, let me use a Python-style approach or a PowerShell cmdlet that can search for URL patterns.\n\nActually, let me use Select-String on just a portion of the binary file, streaming through it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_faeN3FoHOZhJv4GytN4a5363","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use a .NET approach to grep for URLs in the binary - more efficient\n$path = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\lib\\arm64-v8a\\libil2cpp.so\"\n$urlPattern = [regex] 'https?://[a-zA-Z0-9./_-]+'\n\n$fs = [System.IO.File]::OpenRead($path)\n$buffer = New-Object byte[] 1048576  # 1MB chunks\n$results = @()\n\nwhile ($fs.Position -lt $fs.Length) {\n    $bytesRead = $fs.Read($buffer, 0, $buffer.Length)\n    if ($bytesRead -eq 0) { break }\n    \n    # Convert to string (ASCII)\n    $text = [System.Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetString($buffer, 0, $bytesRead)\n    $matches = $urlPattern.Matches($text)\n    foreach ($m in $matches) {\n        if ($m.Value.Length -gt 15 -and $m.Value.Length -lt 120) {\n            $results += $m.Value\n        }\n    }\n}\n$fs.Close()\n\n$results | Sort-Object -Unique | Select-Object -First 60","timeout":120,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":979,"output":468,"cacheRead":75904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77351,"cost":{"input":0.00013706000000000002,"output":0.00013104000000000002,"cacheRead":0.002125312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.