{"type":"message","id":"acf94a73","parentId":"e81ed03b","timestamp":"2026-06-10T10:58:28.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the existing project structure. The settings page has some Chinese encoding issues. Now I need to understand what the user wants. They said \"在我的微信小程序工程中使用相关信息进行微信登录\" - use the relevant information (from the APK analysis) to implement WeChat login in their Mini Program.\n\nLooking at the APK analysis:\n- WeChat App ID: `wxd506e81fe975a813`\n- WeChat App Secret: `e9d5f2b83335c1dbca8b37392ee482cf`\n\nBut wait - the user's Mini Program already has its own appid `wx09786c3fb9eac9a4`. The APK's WeChat credentials belong to the 野狐围棋 app, not the user's Mini Program.\n\nI think the user wants me to:\n1. Use `wx.login()` to get the user's WeChat code\n2. Use the \"相关信息\" (the WeChat AppID and Secret from the APK) to interact with the 野狐围棋 backend\n\nActually wait, let me re-read: \"使用相关信息进行微信登录\" - \"use the relevant information for WeChat login.\" The \"相关信息\" refers to the login flow I analyzed from the APK.\n\nFor a WeChat Mini Program, the standard WeChat login flow is:\n1. `wx.login()` → get code\n2. Send code to own backend → backend calls `https://api.weixin.qq.com/sns/jscode2session` with appid+secret+code → gets openid and session_key\n3. Backend creates custom token and returns to mini program\n\nThe user wants to use the \"相关信息\" - but the information I extracted from the APK is from the 野狐围棋 app, not the user's Mini Program. The user's Mini Program has a different appid.\n\nLet me re-read the user's request more carefully: \"在我的微信小程序工程中使用相关信息进行微信登录\" - \"in my WeChat Mini Program project, use relevant information to implement WeChat login.\"\n\nI think they want me to:\n1. Read the existing project\n2. Use the standard WeChat Mini Program login flow (wx.login() etc.)\n3. Create a login UI and integrate it into the Mini Program\n4. Use their cloudbase backend to handle the code2session exchange\n\nLet me check if there are any cloud functions already set up.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_7qbMhdl2W1jK5rk3QA1Z2105","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check cloud functions\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\projects\\empty-window\\weiqi-sgf\\cloudbase\" -Recurse -Depth 5 | Select-Object Mode, FullName | Sort-Object FullName\n\nWrite-Host \"=== cloud config ===\"\nGet-Content \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\projects\\empty-window\\weiqi-sgf\\miniprogram\\config\\cloud.js\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2008,"output":665,"cacheRead":88192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90865,"cost":{"input":0.00028112000000000005,"output":0.0001862,"cacheRead":0.002469376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002936696}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781089100704,"responseId":"144495d5-c711-4ca1-9c10-942ea96c66b0"}}
