{"type":"message","id":"b633bd9d","parentId":"6ed195f8","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:01:41.214Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No il2cppDumper and no Python. Let me think about alternative approaches:\n\n1. **Download il2cppDumper** from GitHub and use it to extract the metadata\n2. **Use strings on the binary more aggressively** - with a better pattern\n3. **Network capture approach** - run the app and capture traffic\n\nFor option 1, let me check if Node.js is available and try to use the Perfare/Il2CppDumper tool.\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach first - search the libil2cpp.so for URL patterns more carefully by reading it in chunks. The previous attempt used a regex that produced too much noise. Let me look for specific patterns like http:// or https:// followed by domain names.\n\nOr even better, let me search for the known WeChat callback strings that we saw in the Java code - these should be referenced in the Unity code as well. The string \"WXLoginCallback\" appeared in Constants.java. If I search for this string in the SO file, it should tell us where the Unity code references it.\n\nLet me also try a different approach - look at the data files in assets/bin/Data/ - those .extension-less files are likely Unity asset bundles that might contain plain text strings.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_23SYAfBsjsHg5l58HnU25721","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Search for Unity-side callback strings in the binary\n$path = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\lib\\arm64-v8a\\libil2cpp.so\"\n$patterns = @(\n    \"WXLoginCallback\", \"QQLoginCallback\", \"GoogleLoginCallback\",\n    \"WXGetOpenIdCallback\", \"GameManager\",\n    \"foxwq\", \"yhwq\", \"yhwq\\.com\", \"\\.foxwq\",\n    \"api/\", \"/api\", \"/login\", \"/auth\",\n    \"weixin\", \"wechat\", \"qq\\.com\", \"tencent\"\n)\n\nforeach ($pattern in $patterns) {\n    $matches = Select-String -Path $path -Pattern $pattern -SimpleMatch -AllMatches 2>$null\n    if ($matches) {\n        Write-Host \"Found '$pattern':\"\n        $matches | Select-Object -First 5 | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  Line $($_.LineNumber): $($_.Line.Trim())\" }\n    }\n}","timeout":120,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":34,"output":564,"cacheRead":105728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106326,"cost":{"input":0.00000476,"output":0.00015792,"cacheRead":0.002960384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003123064}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781089294146,"responseId":"bb94ff6a-73d1-4b4b-8f3f-e734ddc58b37"}}
