{"type":"message","id":"6ebd6261","parentId":"abeee196","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:02:18.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `Select-String` approach on the 81MB binary file is too slow and produces a lot of noise from embedded function names. The \"api/\" match is just hitting function names with \"api\" in them.\n\nLet me take a completely different approach. Instead of trying to extract strings from the binary file, let me:\n\n1. Download and use `il2cppDumper` (the de facto tool for this) on the metadata and the binary\n2. OR try a more targeted approach\n\nLet me try downloading il2cppDumper from GitHub releases. It's a .NET tool.\n\nActually, there's a tool called `Il2CppDumper` by Perfare. Let me check if I can download and use it quickly.\n\nWait, actually there may be a simpler approach. Let me check if there's a `config` or `json` asset bundle that contains the API URLs. Unity games often store server URLs in text assets or ScriptableObjects.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_zcblxbOg2ryVTnpLdmUG5013","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try a broader string search across ALL asset data files\n$dataDir = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\assets\\bin\\Data\"\n$outputFile = \"$env:TEMP\\urls_in_assets.txt\"\n\n# Search the first 8 data files for URL patterns\nGet-ChildItem $dataDir -File | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 100000 -and $_.Length -lt 10000000 } | Select-Object -First 8 | ForEach-Object {\n    $name = $_.Name\n    $path = $_.FullName\n    $size = $_.Length\n    \n    # Try to extract readable strings\n    $strings = @()\n    $fs = [System.IO.File]::OpenRead($path)\n    $buffer = New-Object byte[] 2097152  # 2MB chunk\n    $bytesRead = $fs.Read($buffer, 0, $buffer.Length)\n    $fs.Close()\n    \n    $sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder\n    $currentLen = 0\n    \n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt [Math]::Min($bytesRead, 2097152); $i++) {\n        $b = $buffer[$i]\n        if ($b -ge 32 -and $b -le 126) {\n            $sb.Append([char]$b) | Out-Null\n            $currentLen++\n        } else {\n            if ($currentLen -ge 8) {\n                $s = $sb.ToString()\n                # Only keep strings that have 'http', 'api', 'login', 'auth', or 'foxwq'\n                if ($s -match 'https?://|\\.com|\\.cn|foxwq|yhwq|login|auth|token|api') {\n                    $strings += $s\n                }\n            }\n            $sb.Clear()\n            $currentLen = 0\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if ($strings.Count -gt 0) {\n        Write-Host \"=== $name ($size bytes) ===\"\n        $strings | Sort-Object -Unique | Select-Object -First 20\n    }\n}","timeout":120,"yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3233,"output":743,"cacheRead":106240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110216,"cost":{"input":0.00045262000000000004,"output":0.00020804000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0029747199999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0036353799999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781089330931,"responseId":"959b9da7-a125-490a-a4fc-eb86bb957153"}}
