{"type":"message","id":"f7712c47","parentId":"0e86e3c0","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:04:15.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the download failed or was killed. Let me try a simpler approach. Instead of downloading Il2CppDumper (which might be complex and time-consuming), let me use a much more practical approach:\n\nSince the 野狐围棋 WeChat Mini Program likely uses the same backend as the mobile app, and based on the APK analysis we know:\n- The app uses a WeChat OAuth flow where the access_token is exchanged on the client side\n- The flow: wx.login() → code → WeChat API (with appid+secret) → access_token+openid → then calls game backend\n\nFor the game backend, typical Unity games store API URLs in config files or ScriptableObjects within the asset bundles. Instead of trying to extract from the compressed bundles, let me try a different approach:\n\n1. Look for common Unity asset bundle structures\n2. Search for config patterns like \"http\" in all data files\n\nActually, let me try a much faster approach - using a simple Node.js or .NET script to scan the data files. But actually the best approach right now might be to look at the larger data files (around 4-8MB) which are likely the Unity \"level\" or \"sharedassets\" bundles that contain serialized data, and try to extract strings from them.\n\nWait, actually, the data files in `assets/bin/Data/` named with hash-like names like `24666b72f0325d742a2c765fa23910cb` are Unity asset bundle files. The ones around 4MB are the \"level0\", \"level1\", etc... but without extensions, it's hard to tell which is which.\n\nActually, a much more pragmatic approach: let me search the libil2cpp.so more efficiently. The strings I should look for are things like:\n- `http://` or `https://` prefixes\n- `.com/` or `.cn/` \n- `api` \n- Common Unity networking library names\n\nLet me try a more efficient approach using PowerShell's .NET string operations.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_IIi5qO4AbXpdBuUJYQaL5193","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Efficient approach: use .NET to find URLs in the binary with better chunk size\n$path = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\lib\\arm64-v8a\\libil2cpp.so\"\n$results = New-Object System.Collections.ArrayList\n\n$fs = [System.IO.File]::OpenRead($path)\n$chunkSize = 209715200  # 200MB - read the whole file at once\n$buffer = New-Object byte[] $chunkSize\n$bytesRead = $fs.Read($buffer, 0, $chunkSize)\n$fs.Close()\n\n# Batch convert to string \n$text = [System.Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetString($buffer, 0, $bytesRead)\n\n# Find all URL-like patterns using regex\n$urlMatches = [regex]::Matches($text, 'https?://[a-zA-Z0-9\\.\\-_]+(?:\\.[a-zA-Z]{2,})+(?:/[a-zA-Z0-9\\.\\-_/~%]*)*(?:\\?[a-zA-Z0-9\\.\\-_=&~%]*)?')\n$urlMatches | ForEach-Object { \n    if ($_.Value.Length -gt 18 -and $_.Value.Length -lt 200 -and \n        $_.Value -notmatch 'w3\\.org|android\\.googlesource|github\\.com|unity3d\\.com|microsoft\\.com|nuget') {\n        [void]$results.Add($_.Value)\n    }\n}\n\n$results | Sort-Object -Unique | Select-Object -First 40","timeout":60,"yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":99,"output":846,"cacheRead":116608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117553,"cost":{"input":0.000013860000000000001,"output":0.00023688000000000002,"cacheRead":0.003265024,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003515764}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781089444894,"responseId":"fc5f2fc9-d67a-4daa-ab25-132dfc679b7b"}}
