{"type":"message","id":"73056c44","parentId":"bb9b04e3","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:04:22.121Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still garbage results. The libil2cpp.so is compiled with obfuscation or the URLs are encrypted/encoded. For IL2CPP, the actual URLs may be stored in the global-metadata.dat (the managed string table) rather than in the binary code itself. Or they might be stored in access-controlled asset bundles.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach:\n1. Look at the `global-metadata.dat` file - it's the IL2CPP metadata that contains all string literals from the C# code\n2. Search for base64-encoded strings in the binary (common pattern for storing URLs in Unity games)\n\nLet me check the global-metadata.dat.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_rVvCQT6ByBFkypd4oItw0164","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# The global-metadata.dat contains the string table from C# code\n# Let's try to extract readable strings from it\n$path = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\assets\\bin\\Data\\Managed\\Metadata\\global-metadata.dat\"\nWrite-Host \"File size: $((Get-Item $path).Length) bytes\"\n\n# Read the whole file and try to extract readable strings\n$fs = [System.IO.File]::OpenRead($path)\n$buffer = New-Object byte[] 10000000  # 10MB\n$bytesRead = $fs.Read($buffer, 0, $buffer.Length)\n$fs.Close()\n\n# Extract strings with min length 6\n$sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder\n$strings = @()\n$currentLen = 0\n$minLen = 6\n\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $bytesRead; $i++) {\n    $b = $buffer[$i]\n    if ($b -ge 32 -and $b -le 126) {\n        $sb.Append([char]$b) | Out-Null\n        $currentLen++\n    } else {\n        if ($currentLen -ge $minLen) {\n            $s = $sb.ToString()\n            # Only keep strings related to login/API/networking\n            if ($s -match 'login|Login|auth|Auth|token|Token|api|Api|\\.com|\\.cn|http|socket|tcp|GameManager|user|password|session') {\n                $strings += $s\n            }\n        }\n        $sb.Clear()\n        $currentLen = 0\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"=== IL2CPP Metadata strings ===\"\n$strings | Sort-Object -Unique | Select-Object -First 60","timeout":60,"yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":83,"output":606,"cacheRead":117504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118193,"cost":{"input":0.00001162,"output":0.00016968000000000002,"cacheRead":0.003290112,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003471412}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781089455765,"responseId":"0928ef0e-c71e-4fa8-ba60-5cbb1aa1d9d3"}}
