{"type":"message","id":"c744ee26","parentId":"eb40a23c","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:07:24.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have some great findings:\n\n**Key domains:**\n- `foxwq.com` (主域名)\n- `edu.foxwq.com` (教育/服务协议)\n- `beian.miit.gov.cn` (ICP备案)\n- `enterprise@foxwq.com` (客服邮箱)\n\n**拍照数子 (Photo Counting) feature strings:**\n- `拍照数子功能在这里` - Photo counting feature is here\n- `开始识别3S` - Start recognition in 3 seconds\n- `请对着棋盘拍照` - Please take photo of board\n- `识别频率过快` - Recognition too frequent\n- `无法识别` - Cannot recognize\n- `当前设备暂不支持拍照数子功能` - Device doesn't support this\n- `拍照取题` - Photo problem fetching\n- `拍照数子(app)` - Photo counting app feature\n\nThe API endpoint for the recognition is unknown from these UI strings alone. It would be in the IL2CPP binary.\n\nBut now I have the domain: `foxwq.com`. Let me also look for the specific server/API subdomains.\n\nActually, let me compile what we know about the infrastructure and search for server URLs in the I18N and FGUI more broadly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EyGvrMlGQHlfJJknLNxC9516","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Search for any server URLs or API paths in all accessible text files\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\assets\" -Recurse -Include \"*.xml\",\"*.csv\",\"*.txt\",\"*.json\",\"*.bytes\" | ForEach-Object {\n    $path = $_.FullName\n    $lines = Get-Content $path -Encoding UTF8 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    $lines | Where-Object { $_ -match \"foxwq|yhwq|\\.com|\\.cn|://|server|Server|api/|socket|tcp|ws://|wss://\" } | ForEach-Object {\n        Write-Host \"$($_.Name): $_\"\n    }\n} | Select-Object -First 30\n\nWrite-Host \"=== Also search for websocket patterns ===\"\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\野狐围棋\\assets\" -Recurse -Include \"*.xml\",\"*.csv\",\"*.json\" | ForEach-Object {\n    $lines = Get-Content $_.FullName -Encoding UTF8 -ErrorAction Silently