{"type":"message","id":"4be8573b","parentId":"b26c50ef","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:52:03.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No Python, no pip, no ADB. The situation is:\n- No Android SDK/emulator\n- No Python (so no mitmproxy directly)\n- we have Node.js and Java\n\nLet me think about the best approach:\n\n**Option 1: Install Android SDK tools + create emulator**\n- Download command-line tools from Google\n- Create AVD\n- This takes a while but is comprehensive\n\n**Option 2: Use Python + mitmproxy**\n- Need to install Python first\n- Then pip install mitmproxy\n- Still need an Android device/emulator\n\n**Option 3: Use Fiddler** (native Windows app, no Python needed)\n- Download and install Fiddler Classic (free, Windows native)\n- Set up HTTPS decryption\n- Connect Android emulator/device\n\n**Option 4: Use Charles Proxy** (Java-based)\n- We already have Java!\n- Download Charles Proxy (shareware, but has free trial)\n- Set up as HTTPS proxy\n- Connect Android device\n\n**Option 5: Use a Node.js-based proxy**\n- We have Node.js available\n- Can use `http-mitm-proxy` or similar\n- But this would be complex to set up\n\nFor the Android emulator, I could:\n1. Install **Android SDK command line tools** (without full Android Studio)\n2. Create an emulator\n3. Install the APK\n\nOR:\n1. Install a lightweight Android emulator like **BlueStacks** or **LDPlayer** via winget\n2. Install the APK\n3. Set up proxy\n\nLet me check winget for Android emulators and Python.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"环境比较空，需要装几个工具。先看看最快路径。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OTmLmCyn36hRawVJfYVA8689","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what winget can offer quickly\nwinget search \"python\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 10\nWrite-Host \"=== wait for it... ===\"\nwinget search \"bluestacks\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 10","timeout":60,"yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"