{"type":"message","id":"3625eb22","parentId":"91e6f8b4","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:52:19.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I can install Python and BlueStacks via winget. But the user specifically said \"好的\" to the network capture approach. Let me think about what's the fastest way.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. For network capturing the 野狐围棋 API:\n\n1. **BlueStacks** - Heavy download (1GB+), takes time to install\n2. **Python + mitmproxy** - Quick to install, lightweight\n3. **Android SDK tools** - Also heavy\n\nActually, the most practical and fastest approach would be:\n1. Install Python quickly via winget (or just install mitmproxy via npm/node.js)\n2. Then we need an Android device\n\nBut wait - we have **Node.js**. There are Node.js HTTP proxy packages that can capture/mitm HTTPS. But the issue is we don't have an Android device or emulator.\n\nLet me try a different approach entirely. Since we have the 野狐围棋 APK, and we know the app uses Unity + IL2CPP, maybe I can use a different approach:\n\n**Actually, wait.** Let me reconsider what the user wants. They said \"逆向工程拍照数字api\" and then \"好的\" meaning they agree to the network capture approach.\n\nBut installing a full Android emulator + proxy setup is going to take a very long time. Let me see if there's a faster way:\n\n**Fast approach:**\n1. Download and run **mitmproxy on the PC** (via pip or npm)\n2. Use **Android emulator** - The quickest option might be to install **MSI App Player** or use the **Windows Subsystem for Android** if available.\n\nActually, let me check if Windows Subsystem for Android is available, as it's the lightest option.\n\nOr, even better: let me install **Scrcpy + connect a real device** if the user has an Android phone.\n\nBut actually, I think the most practical approach given the constraints is:\n1. Install Python via winget (fast)\n2. Install mitmproxy (pip install mitmproxy)\n3. Install Android command-line tools to create an emulator\n\nOr alternatively, skip the emulator and use an approach where we:\n1. Extract and analyze the Unity asset bundles that contain the API endpoints\n2. Use Python to properly parse Unity assets\n\nLet me check if there's il2cpp to parse the binary properly.\n\nActually, let me take the most pragmatic approach: install Python + mitmproxy, and install BlueStacks Android emulator in parallel. This gives the best chance of getting the actual API endpoints.\n\nActually wait - the user said \"好的\" to the network capture approach. Let me just go ahead and start installing the necessary tools. I'll install Python first (for mitmproxy) and BlueStacks (for Android emulation) in parallel.\n\nHmm, but I can't run parallel installs easily. Let me just start with Python + mitmproxy first, then figure out the Android emulator situation.\n\nActually, the fastest approach might be to use **Fiddler Classic** which is a native Windows app. It's a free download from Telerik and comes as a standalone executable. No need for Python or any dependencies.\n\nBut we still need an Android device/emulator.\n\nLet me check if there's a simpler way - can I use **WSAG (Windows Subsystem for Android)**?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PB6sZ9D79CGI9qX1pW003791","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check for Windows Subsystem for Android\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName \"HypervisorPlatform\" 2>$null | Select-Object State\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName \"Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Android\" 2>$null | Select-Object State\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Also check docker / WSL\nwsl --status 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Check if there are any existing Android images/sdks\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.android\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -Depth 0 | Select-Object FullName","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":235,"ou