{"type":"message","id":"e19a3d82","parentId":"3e6779e0","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:55:19.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the CA certificate has been generated. Now I need to:\n\n1. Install the CA cert on the Android emulator\n2. Set the proxy on the emulator\n3. Start the mitmproxy capture\n4. Run the app and use the photo feature\n\nLet me install the CA certificate on the emulator first. For Android, I need to push the certificate to the device and install it.\n\nFor Android 12 (which MuMu emulator runs), the process is:\n1. Push the cert to /sdcard/\n2. Go to Settings → Security → Install certificate from storage\n3. Or use ADB to install it via the certificate installer\n\nLet me also check if the emulator has a display/GUI. I'll need to interact with it visually.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_jYuUm02h5oozZkd7S5Ui2583","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Push the CA cert to emulator\nWrite-Host \"Pushing CA cert...\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 push \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.mitmproxy\\mitmproxy-ca-cert.cer\" /sdcard/ 2>&1\n\n# Check the installed app\nWrite-Host \"=== List packages ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell pm list packages | findstr \"foxwq\" 2>&1\n\n# Get device IP\nWrite-Host \"=== Device IP ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell ip addr show | findstr \"inet \" 2>&1\n\n# Get host PC IP on the emulator's network\nWrite-Host \"=== Host IP ===\"\nipconfig | findstr \"IPv4\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":223,"output":461,"cacheRead":172416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":173100,"cost":{"input":0.00003122,"output":0.00012908,"cacheRead":0.0048276479999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004987948}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092513