{"type":"message","id":"de7cfdcf","parentId":"ff4da4f5","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:55:28.599Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The emulator IP is 10.0.2.15, and the host has IP 192.168.95.85. The CA cert was pushed successfully, and the 野狐围棋 app is installed.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Install the CA certificate on the Android emulator (open Settings → Security → Install from storage)\n2. Configure the Android emulator's WiFi proxy to point to the host\n3. Start mitmproxy on the host\n4. Launch the app and use the photo number feature\n\nThe emulator uses NAT (10.0.2.x), so the gateway is likely 10.0.2.2 (which maps to the host's localhost). \n\nFor MuMu emulator, the proxy settings are typically done through the emulator's network settings.\n\nBut first, I need to install the CA certificate. For Android 12:\n1. I need to use the settings app\n2. Or I can use `adb shell cmd` to install the certificate programmatically\n\nLet me try the programmatic way.\n\nActually, for Android 12 on MuMu, installing a user CA certificate is not enough for app-level HTTPS capture because many apps use SSL pinning. And since the 野狐围棋 Unity app uses IL2CPP, it likely uses UnityWebRequest which respects the system certificate store.\n\nLet me first install the CA cert, then set up the proxy.\n\nFor Android 12 emulator:\n1. Push cert as described\n2. Use `am start -a android.security.action.INSTALL_CERTIFICATE` to start the cert installer\n3. Or navigate via Settings app\n\nHmm, the am start approach doesn't work well on all devices. Let me just use the adb approach:\n\n```\nadb shell am start -a android.intent.action.VIEW -d \"content://com.android.externalstorage.documents/document/primary%3Amitmproxy-ca-cert.cer\" -t \"application/x-x509-ca-cert\"\n```\n\nOr simpler approach for Android 12: use the security settings.\n\nActually, the easiest approach on MuMu might be to:\n1. Use the emulator's UI to install the certificate\n2. Or use `adb shell` to do it\n\nLet me try a different approach. On MuMu emulator, there may be a root shell. Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_a5Vud4rgdmWqwYDEWZ227398","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Check if emulator is rooted\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'whoami'\" 2>&1\n\n# Alternative: try installing via Settings\nWrite-Host \"=== Opening cert installer ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"am start -a android.security.action.INSTALL_CERTIFICATE\" 2>&1\n\n# Also check Android version\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell getprop ro.build.version.sdk 2>&1\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell getprop ro.build.version.release 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":296,"output":751,"cacheRead":173056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":174103,"cost":{"input":0.00004144,"output":0.00021028000000000003,"cacheRead":0.004845568,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005097288}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092519777,"responseId":"e5af89da-29c4-4df5-92ec-eec136be0903"}}
