{"type":"message","id":"461715ec","parentId":"28a9fb1e","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:55:37.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The emulator is rooted (su -c 'whoami' returned \"root\"). Android version is 12 (SDK 32).\n\nSince the emulator is rooted, I can install the CA certificate as a system certificate instead of user certificate. For system certs, the app will trust them by default (even apps with SSL pinning targetting Android N+ with network security config may still trust system certs).\n\nActually, for Android 12, user-installed CA certs are NOT trusted by default for apps targeting API 24+. But system certs ARE trusted.\n\nSince this is a rooted emulator, I can push the certificate to the system trust store:\n```\nadb push mitmproxy-ca-cert.cer /system/etc/security/cacerts/\n```\n\nBut the file needs a specific hash format. Let me generate the hash.\n\nThe format is: `<hash>.0` where hash is the subject hash from OpenSSL.\n\nLet me do this properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"模拟器已 root！直接装系统级 CA 证书。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wxxmCSEp5fQkxQtyMsTz6926","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n$certPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.mitmproxy\\mitmproxy-ca-cert.cer\"\n\n# Convert PEM to the correct format and get hash\n$opensslResult = & \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\..\\..\\..\\NDK\\toolchains\\llvm\\prebuilt\\windows-x86_64\\bin\\openssl.exe\" x509 -inform PEM -subject_hash_old -in $certPath 2>&1\nWrite-Host \"Hash result: $opensslResult\"\n\n# Actually, the cert is in DER format (.cer). Let me convert to PEM first\nWrite-Host \"=== Using Python to generate hash ===\"\npython -c \"\nfrom cryptography import x509\nfrom cryptography.hazmat.primitives import hashes\nimport hashlib\nimport re\n\nwith open('$certPath', 'rb') as f:\n    cert_data = f.read()\n\n# Try to parse as DER\ntry:\n    cert = x509.load_der_x509_certificate(cert_data)\nexcept:\n    cert = x509.load_pem_x509_certificate(cert_data)\n\n# Get subject hash (old format, 8 hex chars)\nsubject = cert.subject.rfc4514_string()\n# Use Python's hashlib to compute similar to openssl -subject_hash_old\n# Actually we need OpenSSL's subject_hash_old which is the hash of the DER encoding of the subject\nsubject_der = cert.subject.public_bytes()\nh = hashlib.sha1(subject_der).hexdigest()[:8]\nprint(f'Subject hash: {h}')\nprint(f'Subject: {subject}')\n\"","timeout":30,"yieldMs":10000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":205,"output":716,"cacheRead":174080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":175001,"cost":{"input":0.000028700000000000003,"output":0.00020048,"cacheRead":0.00487424,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00510342}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092529116,"responseId":"a9d96985-80f4-4d11-9067-cd86eff46c5f"}}
