{"type":"message","id":"0c6f0738","parentId":"1b261f32","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:56:52.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `/system` partition is read-only. Let me try to remount it differently. On Android 12 with AVB (Android Verified Boot), the system partition is verified and read-only. But some MuMu emulators allow mounting it as read-write by modifying the boot image's command line.\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach. On MuMu Player, I can use the emulator's built-in root features:\n1. MuMu Player 12 has a Settings panel where you can enable \"Root\"\n2. And it might have a way to write to system partition\n\nLet me check if there's a writable system image on MuMu.\n\nOr better yet, let me try the `mount -o rw,remount /system` command with `su` in different ways.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach to bypass the read-only system partition:\n\n1. **Use magisk's Magisk OverlayFS**: Mount a writable overlay\n2. **Use `bind mount`**: Mount the cert file over the existing system location\n\nLet me try the bind mount approach:\n```\nsu -c \"mount -o bind /sdcard/c8750f0d.0 /system/etc/security/cacerts/c8750f0d.0\"\n```\n\nWait, that won't work because the target file doesn't exist in the overlay.\n\nActually, a more practical approach: use `magisk` if available, or use `adb shell` to create a Magisk module.\n\nBut the simplest approach might be to use adb to directly interact with the Device Policy Manager to install the cert as a user certificate. Let me try using the Android Keystore manager.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_q0vtW7bxkzgrJg1AYx546712","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Try remount with ro to rw switch via disable-verity\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'disable-verity'\" 2>&1\n# Alternative: try with blockdev\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'blockdev --setrw /dev/block/sda6'\" 2>&1\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'mount -o rw,remount /system'\" 2>&1\n\n# If that works, push the cert\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'cp /sdcard/c8750f0d.0 /system/etc/security/cacerts/'\" 2>&1\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'chmod 644 /system/etc/security/cacerts/c8750f0d.0'\" 2>&1\n\n# Verify\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"ls -la /system/etc/security/cacerts/ | grep c8750\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":4605,"output":737,"cacheRead":181888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":187230,"cost":{"input":0.0006447,"output":0.00020636000000000002,"cacheRead":0.005092864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005943924}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092603546,"responseId":"80a2bc2e-6272-4686-bbc9-52c3037435f4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"63a33185","parentId":"0c6f0738","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:57:02.533Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_q0vtW7bxkzgrJg1AYx546712","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session fast-glade, pid 22588). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"fast-glade","pid":22588,"startedAt":1781092612436,"cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace","tail":"disable-verity only works for userdebug builds\r\nverity cannot be disabled/enabled - USER build\r\n"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781092622533}}
{"type":"message","id":"a29e55b6","parentId":"63a33185","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:57:09.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The command is still running. Let me wait briefly. Actually, I think I should take a different approach. The muMu emulator is likely using a read-only ext4 system partition that can't be easily remounted. Let me try an approach using overlay2 or a bind mount.\n\nActually, wait - the cert is already installed at `/data/misc/user/0/cacerts-added/`. On a rooted device, I can also set the system property to trust user certificates. Or I can use `settings put global development_settings_enabled 1` and then enable some experimental features.\n\nBut actually, the simplest approach for rooted emulators: use Magisk's module system or the adb-overlay approach.\n\nLet me try yet another approach - I'll use MuMu's own tools. Actually, let me check MuMu's configuration.\n\nWait, actually, I think the most practical thing to do at this point is to:\n1. Accept that we can't easily get system-level HTTPS capture on this Android 12 rooted device\n2. Use a different approach: skip the emulator entirely and just use the il2cppDumper tool properly\n\nOR\n\n3. Use a MUCH simpler approach: Use **Frida** to hook the UnityWebRequest API on the device, or  \n4. Use **tcpdump** on the device itself (since it's rooted) to capture all network traffic\n5. Or use the emulator's built-in network capture function\n\nActually, MuMu emulator has a built-in network proxy setting! Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MBkwj77AbZNzJNUYyl674259","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"fast-glade","timeout":15000,"action":"poll"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":139,"output":399,"cacheRead":187136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":187674,"cost":{"input":0.00001946,"output":0.00011172000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0052398079999999994,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005370987999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092622536,"responseId":"b9a9e963-d018-4de2-8dd0-4b55701d9be4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"311ac716","parentId":"a29e55b6","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:57:11.754Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_MBkwj77AbZNzJNUYyl674259","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"disable-verity only works for userdebug builds\r\nverity cannot be disabled/enabled - USER build\n\nProcess exited with signal SIGKILL."}],"details":{"status":"failed","sessionId":"fast-glade","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"disable-verity only works for userdebug builds\r\nverity cannot be disabled/enabled - USER build\r\n","name":"$adb ="},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781092631754}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ffa1b3c","parentId":"311ac716","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:57:22.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"USER build - not userdebug. Can't disable verity. Let me try a completely different approach:\n\n1. Use **tcpdump** on the emulator to capture raw network traffic\n2. Save the pcap file to the host\n3. Analyze with Wireshark\n\nSince the emulator is rooted, I can use `tcpdump` to capture all traffic (unencrypted before TLS). Actually no - tcpdump would capture the TLS encrypted traffic, not the plaintext.\n\nWait - the better approach is to use **routing**: set the Android emulator's default gateway to the host, and run mitmproxy as a transparent proxy on the host. But without the CA cert on the device, HTTPS won't be decrypted.\n\nLet me think of another way... Actually, since the emulator uses the host as its gateway (10.0.2.2), I can:\n1. Start mitmproxy in transparent mode on the host\n2. Configure iptables on the emulator to redirect all traffic to mitmproxy\n3. But we still need the CA cert\n\nOR - we can use **SSL pinning bypass**:\n1. Use Frida to hook the SSL verification\n2. But this is complex and the app uses Unity IL2CPP\n\nActually, the easiest approach at this point is to:\n1. Run the app on the emulator\n2. Capture all network traffic using **PCAPdroid** (an Android app) or use the emulator's native packet capture\n3. Unencrypted HTTP calls will be visible\n4. For HTTPS, look at Server Name Indication (SNI) to find hostnames\n\nActually, let me just use a simple approach: since the emulator has ADB and root, let me install PCAPdroid or a similar traffic capture tool.\n\nOr even simpler: use `tcpdump` which is available on Android devices. Let me try:\n```\nadb shell tcpdump -i any -s 0 -w /sdcard/capture.pcap\n```\n\nThen use the app, stop tcpdump, pull the pcap to host, and analyze it.\n\nBut we may not have tcpdump installed on the emulator. Let me check.\n\nActually, MuMu Player likely doesn't have tcpdump. But we can push a static binary.\n\nWait, this is getting very complex. Let me take a step back and think about what's the fastest way to get what we need.\n\nThe goal is: find the 拍照数子 API endpoint. \n\nOptions:\n1. Install tcpdump/busybox → capture traffic → find API URLs\n2. Use mitmproxy (but needs CA cert in system store, which is difficult on this ROM)\n3. Push a Node.js HTTP proxy to the emulator\n4. Use il2cppDumper properly\n\nLet me try option 4 - download and use il2cppDumper properly this time. I already found the correct download URL.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"系统分区是只读 USER 版，走不了系统 CA。换条路——用 libil2cpp.so 的 il2cppDumper 提取 API。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_smE0gn6LGvEq0REGY4EK1069","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Download Il2CppDumper properly\n$zipUrl = \"https://github.com/Perfare/Il2CppDumper/releases/download/v6.7.46/Il2CppDumper-win-v6.7.46.zip\"\n$zipPath = \"$env:TEMP\\il2cppdumper.zip\"\n$extractPath = \"$env:TEMP\\il2cppdumper\"\n\n# Clean previous\nif (Test-Path $extractPath) { Remove-Item $extractPath -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }\nif (Test-Path $zipPath) { Remove-Item $zipPath -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }\n\nWrite-Host \"Downloading Il2CppDumper...\"\n# Use a simpler download approach\n$wc = New-Object System.Net.WebClient\n$wc.DownloadFile($zipUrl, $zipPath)\nWrite-Host \"Downloaded $((Get-Item $zipPath).Length) bytes\"\n\nExpand-Archive -Path $zipPath -DestinationPath $extractPath -Force\nGet-ChildItem $extractPath | Select-Object Name, Length","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":68,"output":956,"cacheRead":187648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":188672,"cost":{"input":0.00000952,"output":0.00026768,"cacheRead":0.005254144,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005531344}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092631757,"responseId":"d2241662-ca27-46d4-8d96-baa7295ac52a"}}
