{"type":"message","id":"e31ba634","parentId":"d23e1022","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:59:29.755Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Android proxy is set to `10.0.2.2:8080` which points to the host's mitmproxy. But the CA certificate isn't installed in the system trust store. For the program to work, the CA cert needs to be trusted. Since we can't install it in the system store (read-only system), the HTTPS calls will fail with SSL errors.\n\nBut wait - this is actually useful! Even if HTTPS fails, we'll still see:\n1. The hostname from the SSL handshake (SNI)\n2. Any HTTP (non-HTTPS) calls\n3. Any DNS lookups the app makes\n\nAnd some Unity apps make their initial API calls over HTTP before upgrading to HTTPS. Let me verify this is working by checking mitmweb.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The 野狐围棋 app is a game/app that won't work with a self-signed CA cert. If the proxy intercepts HTTPS traffic with mitmproxy's CA, the app will show SSL errors and might crash or show a network error.\n\nBut the key information we want is the **API hostname**. Even if SSL fails, the SNI (Server Name Indication) in the TLS handshake will reveal the hostname.\n\nLet me check if mitmweb is showing any traffic. Actually, the traffic won't go through mitmproxy because the app's SSL library will reject the mitmproxy certificate. But the connection attempt itself might give us useful info.\n\nActually, mitmproxy captures the hostname from the CONNECT request even if the SSL handshake fails. So I should be able to see the server hostnames.\n\nLet me wait a few seconds and then check mitmweb for captured traffic.\n\nBut I should also check - was the mitmweb process started and is it still running? Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_iWK44OxiSgXmZ2N2mQsA8374","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check mitmproxy is still running\nGet-Process -Name \"python*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, @{N='CmdLine';E={$_.CommandLine}} | Out-String -Width 200\n\n# Check if the proxy port is still listening\nnetstat -an | findstr \"8080\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 3\n\n# Check mitmweb availability\ntry {\n    $resp = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    Write-Host \"mitmweb: $($resp.StatusCode) ($($resp.Content.Length) bytes)\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"mitmweb: Not accessible - $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":183,"output":615,"cacheRead":193280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":194078,"cost":{"input":0.000025620000000000002,"output":0.0001722,"cacheRead":0.00541184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005609660000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092761955,"responseId":"88fe3c38-4bc4-45a3-9766-b2c2778db5be"}}
