{"type":"message","id":"fa8062bf","parentId":"dcbcce66","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:59:35.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"mitmweb is running but returns 403 because it needs the token. The proxy port 8080 is also active with an established connection (probably the mitmweb process connecting to the proxy). \n\nLet me check if we can see captured flows using the mitmproxy API.\n\nSince we can't easily access mitmweb UI from this CLI environment, let me use the mitmproxy's API to query the captured flows.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Instead of trying to set up a complex man-in-the-middle setup with CA certificates and all that, I should:\n\n1. Use `tcpdump` on the emulator (since it's rooted) to capture raw packets\n2. Analyze the packet captures to find hostnames and API URLs\n3. We don't need to decrypt TLS - just seeing the SNI and DNS queries tells us the API hosts\n\nLet me push a static tcpdump binary to the emulator.\n\nActually wait - another approach: use the logcat output. Unity apps often print log messages that contain HTTP request URLs.\n\nLet me check the logcat for any HTTP-related logs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_90UeP4XGTOWawuVi2UK60895","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Check logcat for network-related logs from the app\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 logcat -d | Select-String -Pattern \"foxwq|yhwq|Unity|http|HTTP|api|Auth|upload|photo|Photo|recogn\" | Select-Object -First 30","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":175,"output":408,"cacheRead":194048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":194631,"cost":{"input":0.000024500000000000003,"output":0.00011424,"cacheRead":0.005433344,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005572084}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timest