{"type":"message","id":"1b03fe47","parentId":"7710107e","timestamp":"2026-06-10T11:59:45.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logcat output is mostly system-level logs and doesn't contain the app-specific network logs. That's because:\n1. I need to filter by the app's PID\n2. The app hasn't made any network requests yet (we just launched it and it may have SSL verification issues with mitmproxy)\n\nLet me try a different approach. Let me:\n1. Check if there's a tcpdump/busybox installed or push a static binary\n2. Capture some packet traffic\n3. Look for SNI hostnames\n\nOR - let me try the simplest possible approach: check the DNS resolver on the emulator for any cached entries related to the app.\n\nActually, let me take a step way back. I've been trying many complex approaches. Let me try the most direct approach I can think of:\n\nSince we have `adb root` access, let me:\n1. Remove the proxy setting (to let the app work normally)\n2. Run the app and use the photo feature\n3. Dump the DNS cache or use a simple network monitoring approach\n\nActually, I just realized something. I already have the proxy configured. Let me just try to use the app with it and see if it works. If the app sends HTTP requests, mitmproxy will capture them. If it's HTTPS with SSL verification, the app will fail to connect and show an error.\n\nLet me clear the logs, run the app, and look for Unity debug logs in logcat.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KHU6zUtsKkZIKveef7l17671","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Clear logcat and restart the app\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 logcat -c 2>&1\n\n# Use am start to launch the main activity directly\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"am start -n com.foxwq.yhwq/com.foxwq.yhwq.MainActivity\" 2>&1\n\n# Wait for the app to load and make network requests\nStart-Sleep 8\n\n# Capture Unity/Debug logs\nWrite-Host \"=== App logs (Unity/network related) ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 logcat -d -s \"Unity\" \"FSDK\" \"YHWQ\" \"DEBUG\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 40\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== DNS queries ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'dumpsys netstats'\" 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern \"foxwq|yhwq|\\.com|\\.cn\" | Select-Object -First 20","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1408,"output":665,"cacheRead":194560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":196633,"cost":{"input":0.00019712,"output":0.0001862,"cacheRead":0.00544768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005831}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092776253,"responseId":"6d790285-22cc-4cbb-b200-1df54e4af7fd"}}
