{"type":"message","id":"827d9d50","parentId":"1a5e0757","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:00:00.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great! I can see Unity logs in logcat! The app's Unity tag provides useful debug output. Let me now interact with the app - use the photo number feature and capture more logs with network-related content.\n\nBut I can't interact with the app's UI through ADB alone. I need a way to:\n1. See the emulator screen \n2. Touch on specific UI elements\n\nLet me check if I can use `uiautomator` or `input tap` to navigate through the app. Or I can try to use scrcpy or the MuMu's built-in screen viewer.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Since I can see Unity logs, and the app connects to a server, let me just wait for the app to start connecting. If there are any HTTP requests happening, the mitmproxy will capture them (for HTTPS, it'll capture the CONNECT hostname even if the SSL handshake fails).\n\nLet me check the mitmproxy flows via its API.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UAT4tbBatghc1RJuxFG35754","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check mitmproxy's captured flows via API\ntry {\n    $flows = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/flows\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    Write-Host \"Flows API: $($flows.StatusCode)\"\n    $flows.Content | Out-File \"$env:TEMP\\mitmflows.json\"\n    Write-Host \"Saved to $(Get-Item \"$env:TEMP\\mitmflows.json\" | Select-Object Length)\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"API error: $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}\n\n# Also check the /dumps endpoint\ntry {\n    $dumps = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/dumps\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    Write-Host \"Dumps API: $($dumps.StatusCode)\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"Dumps API error: $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}\n\n# Check raw mitmproxy log via HTTP\ntry {\n    $resp = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5 -Headers @{\"Authorization\"=\"Bearer 9e265f6c9876bfee9888847a90fe061f\"}\n    Write-Host \"mitmweb root: $($resp.StatusCode)\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"mitmweb root error: $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":786,"output":590,"cacheRead":196608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":197984,"cost":{"input":0.00011004000000000001,"output":0.0001652,"cacheRead":0.005505024,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005780264}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092793775,"responseId":"20698386-e80b-456d-9bec-54d82ac62d04"}}
