{"type":"message","id":"a4d18ea8","parentId":"dc8555ae","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:00:07.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK the mitmweb is running but the API requires authentication. Let me use the mitmproxy's `--set web_username=user --set web_password=pass` or use the token.\n\nWait, looking at mitmweb 12.x, the API might use a different approach. Let me check the flows using the flow reading API.\n\nActually, the mitmproxy Python API can also be used to read flow files. But the easiest way is to add an API token filter.\n\nLet me try a different approach - let me use mitmproxy's `--save-stream-file` option to save all flows to a file, then read that file.\n\nActually, let me take the most practical approach. I'll:\n1. Restart mitmweb with the token in the URL\n2. Access the flows via the API\n\nWait, actually the token should be passed as a query parameter based on mitmproxy docs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nyGQMjHoeuobCUwixhF26312","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try mitmweb API with token as parameter\n$token = \"9e265f6c9876bfee9888847a90fe061f\"\n$flowsUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/flows?token=$token\"\n\ntry {\n    $flows = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $flowsUrl -TimeoutSec 5\n    Write-Host \"Flows: Count=$($flows.Count)\"\n    $flows | ForEach-Object {\n        Write-Host \"  $($_.request.method) $($_.request.host)$($_.request.path)\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"Flows API error: $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}\n\n# Also try the newer mitmweb event stream endpoint\ntry {\n    $streamUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/events?token=$token\"\n    $stream = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $streamUrl -TimeoutSec 3\n    Write-Host \"Events: $($stream.Count)\"\n    $stream | Select-Object -First 10\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"Events API error: $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"in