{"type":"message","id":"bc04c885","parentId":"d2395b4c","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:00:31.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only one flow recorded - the MuMu emulator's own update check. The 野狐围棋 app hasn't made any network requests through the proxy. This could be because:\n1. The app is still loading/splash screen\n2. The app's SSL verification is failing with mitmproxy's certificate\n3. The app hasn't reached the login/main screen yet\n\nThe Unity logs show \"ChannelMgr OnApplicationPause\" and \"JPushPlugin\" - the app was paused/resumed when I re-launched it.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to capture with mitmproxy (which requires SSL trust), let me:\n1. Remove the proxy settings (so the app can connect normally)\n2. Use a simpler tool to see just the DNS queries and connection attempts\n\nWait, actually I have an even better idea. Let me:\n1. Remove the proxy setting\n2. Use `iptables` to log all TCP connections without intercepting them\n3. This will show us the hostnames the app connects to\n\nOr even simpler: let me use `strace` on the app process to see connect() calls.\n\nLet me try the iptables logging approach with CONFIG_NETFILTER_XT_MARK:\n```\niptables -I OUTPUT -p tcp -m owner --uid-owner [APP_UID] -j LOG --log-prefix \"FOXWQ_NET: \"\n```\n\nLet me get the app's UID and set this up.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LxJvbGtOFa0blgiBVqHA6680","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Remove proxy first so the app can connect normally\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"settings put global http_proxy :0\" 2>&1\n\n# Get the app UID\n$uidInfo = & $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'cat /proc/3959/status | grep Uid'\" 2>&1\nWrite-Host \"App UID: $uidInfo\"\n\n# Use iptables to log all connections from the app\n$appUid = ($uidInfo -split '\\s+')[1]\nWrite-Host \"Found UID=$appUid\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'iptables -I OUTPUT 1 -p tcp -m owner --uid-owner $appUid -j LOG --log-prefix FOXWQ_CONNECT'\" 2>&1\n\n# Clear logcat and restart the app\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 logcat -c 2>&1\n\n# Kill and restart the app\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"am force-stop com.foxwq.yhwq\" 2>&1\nStart-Sleep 1\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"monkey -p com.foxwq.yhwq -c android.intent.category.LAUNCHER 1\" 2>&1\n\n# Wait for the app to fully load\nWrite-Host \"Waiting 15 seconds for app to load...\"\nStart-Sleep 15\n\n# Check for network connection logs\nWrite-Host \"=== Network Connections (iptables + logcat) ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 logcat -d | Select-String -Pattern \"FOXWQ_CONNECT|kernel|IN=\" | Select-Object -First 30\n\n# Also try dmesg\nWrite-Host \"=== dmesg ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'dmesg | grep FOXWQ'\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 20","timeout":40}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":700,"output":919,"cacheRead":199552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":201171,"cost":{"input":0.00009800000000000001,"output":0.00025732,"cacheRead":0.005587456,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005942776}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092819617,"responseId":"0372f1b2-37aa-4699-833f-e67879fe0509"}}
