{"type":"message","id":"881a34a2","parentId":"5d67b69f","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:01:40.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the IP addresses the app is connecting to! No PTR records for reverse DNS, but I can try to look up these IPs:\n\n1. `211.254.112.193` - This is the app's server (from UID 10042 = com.foxwq.yhwq)\n2. `44.49.101.180` - Server on port 443 and 80\n3. `146.122.236.115` - Another server on port 443\n\nLet me search the web to find which domain these belong to.\n\nActually, let me try to lookup whois info for these IPs, or search for them.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KlTRYXDtFUaM1XVmNMbN8704","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check IP locations and owners\n$ips = @(\"211.254.112.193\", \"44.49.101.180\", \"146.122.236.115\")\n\nforeach ($ip in $ips) {\n    try {\n        # Try to get more info about the IP\n        $rdns = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostEntry($ip) 2>$null\n        Write-Host \"$ip → $($rdns.HostName)\"\n    } catch {\n        Write-Host \"$ip → no PTR\"\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== IP Geolocation ===\"\n# Use whois-like approach via web\nforeach ($ip in $ips) {\n    try {\n        $result = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://ip-api.com/json/$ip\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n        $json = $result.Content | ConvertFrom-Json\n        Write-Host \"$ip → $($json.country) $($json.regionName) $($json.city) ($($json.org) / $($json.isp))\"\n    } catch {\n        Write-Host \"$ip → lookup failed: $_\"\n    }\n}","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":318,"output":449,"cacheRead":207104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":207871,"cost":{"input":0.00004452,"output":0.00012572,"cacheRead":0.005798912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005969152}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092893023,"responseId":"29d951e4-f3d3-4b10-84d9-47e77ec54e25"}}
