{"type":"message","id":"d7a6b574","parentId":"3763ea4f","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:01:58.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web lookup is timing out. Let me try a simpler approach - use curl or the built-in capabilities.\n\nActually, since the web seems unavailable (GitHub was also timing out), I'll need to rely on the information I already have.\n\nLet me summarize what I've found and present it to the user. The key findings are:\n\n1. **App uses PullConfigFromServer CONFIG_HTTP** - a config-based approach\n2. **Known domains from the APK**: `foxwq.com`, `edu.foxwq.com`\n3. **Server IPs** (detected via packet analysis):\n   - `211.254.112.193:443` - Main game server (foxwq)\n   - `44.49.101.180:443` - Another server\n   - `146.122.236.115:443` - Third server\n\n4. **The API endpoints are in the IL2CPP binary** which needs proper tools (il2cppDumper + IDA Pro) to extract\n5. **Unity logs show**:\n   - `DynamicIPConfigManger` - Dynamic IP configuration\n   - `PullAndSaveServerConfig` - Server config pulling\n   - `FetchCommonInfoConfig FGWTokenIsNull` - Token-based auth\n   - `DelayGetAppStoreCountry` - App store check\n\nThe most useful thing I can offer at this point is:\n1. The full list of server IPs\n2. The ability to capture the actual HTTP request body/response by using mitmproxy with the emulator's root (if we can get the CA cert accepted)\n3. Or the user can try to use the api.foxwq.com domain and probe for endpoints\n\nLet me also try to check if the foxwq.com domain resolves to any of these IPs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2KLKLI4gkV6HdIbAgcxM9103","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if foxwq domains resolve to the detected IPs\ntry {\n    $ips = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostAddresses(\"foxwq.com\")\n    Write-Host \"foxwq.com → $($ips -join ', ')\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"foxwq.com → resolve failed\"\n}\n\ntry {\n    $ips = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostAddresses(\"www.foxwq.com\")\n    Write-Host \"www.foxwq.com → $($ips -join ', ')\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"www.foxwq.com → resolve failed\"\n}\n\ntry {\n    $ips = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostAddresses(\"api.foxwq.com\")\n    Write-Host \"api.foxwq.com → $($ips -join ', ')\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"api.foxwq.com → resolve failed\"\n}\n\ntry {\n    $ips = [System.Net.Dns]::GetHostAddresses(\"gateway.foxwq.com\")\n    Write-Host \"gateway.foxwq.com → $($ips -join ', ')\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"gateway.foxwq.com → resolve failed\"\n}","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":173,"output":707,"cacheRead":207744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":208624,"cost":{"input":0.000024220000000000002,"output":0.00019796,"cacheRead":0.005816832,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006039012}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781092910126,"responseId":"5a9393a4-4abd-464d-a1f0-b48ebe2d3368"}}
