{"type":"message","id":"5b2a6436","parentId":"4d8d9da1","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:02:04.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have confirmed:\n- `foxwq.com` / `www.foxwq.com` → 159.75.191.218\n- `api.foxwq.com` → 134.175.211.110\n\nThese are different from the IPs detected from the emulator connections (211.254.112.193, 44.49.101.180, 146.122.236.115). The detected IPs might be game server IPs that are dynamically assigned.\n\nLet me now get all the flows from mitmproxy to see what HTTPS connections the app actually makes. Since mitmproxy is running, even though the SSL handshake might fail (because the cert isn't trusted), the CONNECT requests will still be captured.\n\nLet me also try to poll the flows API again now that the app has been running for a while.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VG60RtM1rRLccKc2ecIx7816","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$token = \"9e265f6c9876bfee9888847a90fe061f\"\n$flowsUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:8081/flows?token=$token\"\n\ntry {\n    $flows = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $flowsUrl -TimeoutSec 5\n    Write-Host \"=== All captured flows ($($flows.Count)) ===\"\n    $flows | ForEach-Object {\n        $method = $_.request.method\n        $hostname = $_.request.host\n        $path = $_.request.path\n        $status = $_.response.status_code\n        $err = $_.error\n        $type = $_.request.scheme\n        Write-Host \"$method $type://$hostname$path → HTTP $status $(if($err){'ERROR: '+$err})\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Host \"Error: $_\"\n}\n\n# Also check if the app made any requests that can give us endpoints\n# Look at what mitmproxy captured that's NOT the MuMu check\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Non-MuMu flows ===\"\n$flows | Where-Object { $_.request.host -notmatch \"mumu|netease|163\" } | ForEach-Object {\n    Write-Host \"$($_.request.method) $($_.request.scheme)://$($_.request.host)$($_.request.path)\"\n}","timeout":10}}],"api":"open