{"type":"message","id":"5b92142b","parentId":"cd20c643","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:57:36.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No output means none of the algorithms worked with the known appids. The decryption approach needs more work.\n\nLet me try a different approach. There's a well-known tool called `wxappUnpacker` that works. But I can't install it from npm or download from GitHub. Let me look for alternative methods.\n\nActually, there's another approach - I can try to use the `unwxapkg` tool or write a more complete decryption routine.\n\nThe standard decryption for V1MMWX (from the open source community) is:\n\n```python\nfrom Crypto.Cipher import AES\nimport hashlib\n\ndef decrypt(app_id, data):\n    key = hashlib.pbkdf2_hmac(app_id, app_id, 1000, 32, hashlib.sha256)\n    iv = key[:16]\n    actual_key = key[16:32]\n    cipher = AES.new(actual_key, AES.MODE_CBC, iv)\n    return cipher.decrypt(data)\n```\n\nOr the simpler version:\n```python\nkey = hashlib.sha256(app_id.encode('utf-8')).digest()[:16]\niv = hashlib.sha256((app_id + 'auth').encode('utf-8')).digest()[:16]\n```\n\nLet me look for the actual algorithm more carefully. The most common reference is from the `wechat-app-unpack` project.\n\nActually, I just recalled - the wxapkg decryption for V1 format uses:\n1. First 6 bytes: header\n2. Remaining: AES-256-CBC encrypted\n3. Key = sha256(appid).slice(0, 16)\n4. IV = sha256(appid + 'sandbox').slice(0, 16)\n\nWait no, those are for other versions. Let me try another known approach:\n\nFor WeChat 8.0+ (V1MMWX format), the key derivation is:\n```\nenc_key = sha256(appid)[16:32]  # bytes 16-31\nenc_iv = sha256(appid)[0:16]    # bytes 0-15\n```\n\nLet me try this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_edl0n0iWdvRZepSZboUS1814","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$script = @'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst crypto = require('crypto');\n\nconst pkg = fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw.wxapkg');\n\nfunction tryDecrypt(appid, algo) {\n    try {\n        let key, iv, name;\n        \n        if (algo === 'sha256_split') {\n            const hash = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid, 'utf8').digest();\n            iv = hash.slice(0, 16);\n            key = hash.slice(16, 32);\n            name = 'sha256_split';\n        } else if (algo === 'sha256_iv_sandbox') {\n            key = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            iv = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid + 'sandbox').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            name = 'sha256_sandbox';\n        } else if (algo === 'sha256_iv_auth') {\n            key = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            iv = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid + 'auth').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            name = 'sha256_auth';\n        } else if (algo === 'md5_iv') {\n            const salt1 = 'd24104997ed56929c0ab6ac4ffacb5f8';\n            const salt2 = '4d32e6d5703327aaf67ce1e3490e294c';\n            key = crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid + salt2).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            iv = crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid + salt1).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            name = 'md5_salted';\n        }\n\n        const encrypted = pkg.slice(6);\n        \n        // Try AES-128-CBC (16 byte key)\n        const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key, iv);\n        const decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(encrypted), decipher.final()]);\n        \n        const check = decrypted.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8');\n        if (check.includes('{') || check.includes('app') || check.includes('page') || check.includes('\\\\n')) {\n            console.log(`✅ ${name} with ${appid}: SUCCESS`);\n            console.log('First:', check.slice(0, 100));\n            return decrypted;\n        }\n    } catch(e) {\n        // expected for wrong keys\n    }\n    return null;\n}\n\n// Try multiple appids with multiple algorithms\nconst appids = [\n    'wx09786c3fb9eac9a4',\n    'wxd506e81fe975a813',\n    'wx5a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b',\n    'wx0c0b55f36d2f7c57',\n    'wx8a9b0c1d2e3f4a5b',\n    'wx6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b',\n    'wx4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c',\n    'wx2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c',\n    'wx',\n    'test',\n];\n\nconst algos = ['sha256_split', 'sha256_sandbox', 'sha256_auth', 'md5_iv'];\n\nfor (const appid of appids) {\n    for (const algo of algos) {\n        const result = tryDecrypt(appid, algo);\n        if (result) {\n            const outPath = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decrypted.wxapkg';\n            fs.writeFileSync(outPath, result);\n            process.exit(0);\n        }\n    }\n}\nconsole.log('All attempts failed');\n'@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt2.js\" -Value $script -Encoding utf8\nnode \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt2.js\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":72,"output":1444,"cacheRead":232576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":234092,"cost":{"input":0.00001008,"output":0.00040432,"cacheRead":0.006512128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0069265279999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096241509,"responseId":"f6978d54-68de-4b2c-b754-e0b77a967532"}}
