{"type":"message","id":"f87153cd","parentId":"d3fa024e","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:57:56.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All decryption attempts failed. The encrypted format might be different than what I expected. Let me take a completely different approach.\n\nSince brute-forcing the appid isn't working, let me check if the file was already decrypted (maybe it's just the raw data, not encrypted in the traditional sense). Or let me check if it's a different format version.\n\nActually, looking at the header again: `56-31-4D-4D-57-58` = `V1MMWX`\n\nFor \"V1\" format wxapkg, the decryption algorithm used by the official `wxappUnpacker` tool is:\n\n1. First 6 bytes: magic header `V1MMWX`\n2. Next bytes: encrypted with AES-CBC\n3. Key = sha256(appid).slice(0, 16)\n4. IV = sha256(appid).slice(16, 32)\n\nWait, I already tried that. Let me double-check my implementation.\n\nActually, I realize the issue - the decryption might need different parameters. Let me look at the actual source code of wxappUnpacker for the exact algorithm.\n\nThe well-known `barnosoft/wxappUnpacker` tool uses:\n```javascript\nvar decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', \n    crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid).digest(), \n    crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid).digest()\n);\n```\n\nWait no, the actual code is more nuanced. Let me check specific versions.\n\nActually, the issue is that I might be using the wrong algorithm. Some versions use:\n\n```javascript\nconst key = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(`${appid}:salt_v2`).digest()\nconst iv = crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid).digest()\nconst decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key.slice(16, 32), iv.slice(0, 16))\n```\n\nLet me also try just assuming the file isn't encrypted at all - some versions are just compressed not encrypted.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6kFtKI0MAu7jFA5ckQnA1079","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$script = @'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst crypto = require('crypto');\nconst zlib = require('zlib');\n\nconst pkg = fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw.wxapkg');\nconsole.log('File size:', pkg.length);\n\n// Approach 1: Try to decompress directly (some wxapkg are just compressed, not encrypted)\nconst compressed = pkg.slice(6);\ntry {\n    const decompressed = zlib.inflateSync(compressed);\n    console.log('Approach 1 (inflate):', decompressed.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8'));\n} catch(e) {\n    console.log('Approach 1 failed:', e.message);\n}\n\ntry {\n    const decompressed = zlib.gunzipSync(compressed);\n    console.log('Approach 1 (gunzip):', decompressed.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8'));\n} catch(e) {\n    console.log('Approach 1 gunzip failed:', e.message);\n}\n\n// Approach 2: try deflate\ntry {\n    const decompressed = zlib.inflateRawSync(compressed);\n    console.log('Approach 1 (inflateRaw):', decompressed.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8'));\n} catch(e) {\n    console.log('Approach 1 inflateRaw failed:', e.message);\n}\n\n// Approach 3: The REAL wxappUnpacker algorithm \n// For WeChat 7.0.3+ (V1MMWX):\n// EncKey = SHA256(AppID)[16:32]\n// EncIV = SHA256(AppID)[0:16]\n// But sometimes it's reversed!\n\nconst appids = [\n    'wx09786c3fb9eac9a4',\n    'wxd506e81fe975a813',\n    'wx0c0b55f36d2f7c57',\n    'wx2a5b6c7d8e9f0a1b',\n    'wx1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b',\n];\n\nfor (const appid of appids) {\n    for (const reversed of [false, true]) {\n        try {\n            const hash = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid, 'utf8').digest();\n            const key = reversed ? hash.slice(0, 16) : hash.slice(16, 32);\n            const iv = reversed ? hash.slice(16, 32) : hash.slice(0, 16);\n            \n            const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key, iv);\n            const decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(compressed), decipher.final()]);\n            \n            // Try to decompress decrypted data\n            try {\n                const decomp = zlib.inflateSync(decrypted);\n                const text = decomp.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8');\n                if (text.includes('{') || text.includes('app') || text.includes('page') || text.includes('.js')) {\n                    console.log(`\\n✅ SUCCESS with ${appid}${reversed ? ' (reversed)' : ''}`);\n                    console.log('First 200 chars:', text);\n                    fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decrypted.wxapkg', decomp);\n                    process.exit(0);\n                }\n            } catch(e) {\n                // Try as raw (not compressed)\n                const text = decrypted.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8');\n                if (text.includes('{') || text.includes('app') || text.includes('page')) {\n                    console.log(`\\n✅ SUCCESS (raw) with ${appid}${reversed ? ' (reversed)' : ''}`);\n                    console.log('First 200 chars:', text);\n                    fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decrypted.wxapkg', decrypted);\n                    process.exit(0);\n                }\n            }\n        } catch(e) {}\n    }\n}\n\nconsole.log('\\nAll decryption attempts failed.');\n\n// Debug: look at the raw bytes more carefully\nconsole.log('\\nFile structure analysis:');\nconsole.log('Header:', pkg.slice(0, 6).toString('hex'), pkg.slice(0, 6).toString());\nconsole.log('Byte 6-10:', pkg.slice(6, 10).toString('hex'));\nconsole.log('Byte 10-20:', pkg.slice(10, 20).toString('hex'));\n\n// Try to find any plaintext in random locations\nfor (let offset = 0; offset < pkg.length; offset += 100000) {\n    const slice = pkg.slice(offset, offset + 100).toString('utf8');\n    if (slice.match(/[a-zA-Z0-9_\\/\\.]{4,}/)) {\n        const cleaned = slice.replace(/[^ -~]/g, '.');\n        if (cleaned.match(/[a-zA-Z]{4,}/)) {\n            console.log(`\\nOffset ${offset}: ${cleaned.slice(0, 80)}`);\n        }\n    }\n}\n'@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt3.js\" -Value $script -Encoding utf8\nnode \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt3.js\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1531,"output":1675,"cacheRead":232576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":235782,"cost":{"input":0.00021434,"output":0.000469,"cacheRead":0.006512128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007195468}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096257286,"responseId":"ae6d9d02-827d-4670-a6a0-27756a1c10d0"}}
