{"type":"message","id":"4fa2519a","parentId":"10a73a0e","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:58:11.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The data at various offsets shows encrypted/garbled content, which confirms the file is strongly encrypted. The raw data at offset 0 with readable chars like DBQ^CV_B] suggests AES encryption with a standard CBC mode.\n\nThe decryption is failing because I don't have the correct appid. \n\nLet me try yet another approach. Instead of trying to decrypt the entire file, let me try common known decryption approaches specifically for WeChat 8.0+ wxapkg. The algorithm has changed over different WeChat versions.\n\nActually, I think I need to try a completely different approach. Let me look for the appid by:\n1. Searching the user's WeChat developer tools for any reference to the wxapkg\n2. Or trying known possible appids from the Go community\n3. Or using a trial-and-error approach with common appid patterns\n\nActually, wait - let me check if there's any cached data about this wxapkg in the WeChat dev tools.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2mQjXG7DKZtPN6Angk2G5176","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$script = @'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst crypto = require('crypto');\nconst pkg = fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw.wxapkg');\n\n// Let me try the EXACT algorithm from the original wechat-app-unpack project\n// The correct algorithm for V1MMWX:\nconst appids = [\n    'wx09786c3fb9eac9a4',\n    'wxd506e81fe975a813',\n    'wxe72d07c8d2d8c8f2',\n    'wx8a9b0c1d2e3f4a5b',\n    'wx6dbd315a0b66b0c2',\n    'wx12a6b7c8d9e0f1a2',\n    'wx9a4b2c5d6e7f8a9b',\n    'wx3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d',\n    'wx4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f',\n];\n\nconst encrypted = pkg.slice(6);\n\nfor (const appid of appids) {\n    // Algorithm 1: The EXACT one from wxappUnpacker\n    try {\n        const key = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid).digest();\n        const iv = crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid).digest().slice(0, 16);\n        \n        // Try with key slice [0:16] and [16:32]\n        for (const keySlice of [0, 16]) {\n            try {\n                const actualKey = key.slice(keySlice, keySlice + 16);\n                const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', actualKey, iv);\n                const decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(encrypted), decipher.final()]);\n                \n                // Try decompress\n                try {\n                    const decomp = require('zlib').inflateSync(decrypted);\n                    const text = decomp.slice(0, 300).toString('utf8');\n                    if (text.includes('.js') || text.includes('.json') || text.includes('app') || text.includes('page') || text.includes('component')) {\n                        console.log(`✅ ${appid} keySlice=${keySlice}: DECRYPTED!`);\n                        console.log('First 300 chars:', text.slice(0, 300));\n                        fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decrypted.wxapkg', decomp);\n                        process.exit(0);\n                    }\n                } catch(e) {\n                    // check raw\n                    const text = decrypted.slice(0, 300).toString('utf8');\n                    if (text.includes('.json') || text.includes('.js') || text.match(/\\w+\\.(js|json|wxml|wxss)/)) {\n                        console.log(`✅ ${appid} keySlice=${keySlice} (raw): DECRYPTED!`);\n                        console.log(text.slice(0, 300));\n                        process.exit(0);\n                    }\n                }\n            } catch(e) {}\n        }\n        \n        // Algorithm 2: reverse key/iv \n        try {\n            const key = crypto.createHash('md5').update(appid).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            const iv = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(appid).digest().slice(0, 16);\n            const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key, iv);\n            const decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(encrypted), decipher.final()]);\n            const decomp = require('zlib').inflateSync(decrypted);\n            const text = decomp.slice(0, 300).toString('utf8');\n            if (text.includes('.json') || text.includes('.js')) {\n                console.log(`✅ ${appid} (algo 2): DECRYPTED!`);\n                fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decrypted.wxapkg', decomp);\n                process.exit(0);\n            }\n        } catch(e) {}\n        \n    } catch(e) {}\n}\n\n// Algorithm from wechat-app-unpack on newer versions:\n// key = sha256(appid).slice(0, 16)\n// Actually, there's also a version where it uses pbkdf2\ntry {\n    const key = crypto.pbkdf2Sync('wx09786c3fb9eac9a4', 'salt', 1000, 16, 'sha1');\n    const iv = Buffer.alloc(16, 0);\n    const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key, iv);\n    const decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(encrypted), decipher.final()]);\n    const decomp = require('zlib').inflateSync(decrypted);\n    console.log('✅ PBKDF2: DECRYPTED!', decomp.slice(0, 200).toString('utf8'));\n    process.exit(0);\n} catch(e) {}\n\nconsole.log('All attempts exhausted. Need the correct appid.');\n'@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt4.js\" -Value $script -Encoding utf8\nnode \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt4.js\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2934,"output":1433,"cacheRead":235776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":240143,"cost":{"input":0.00041076000000000003,"output":0.00040124000000000003,"cacheRead":0.006601727999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007413728}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096276363,"responseId":"1fc945eb-24c7-4ce4-b3e5-c00612e9e4b3"}}
