{"type":"message","id":"0d3644de","parentId":"6ecb899b","timestamp":"2026-06-10T12:59:47.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user doesn't know the appid. I need to find it. Let me try to brute-force it or find it from the file itself.\n\nOne approach: The wxapkg may have the appid embedded in it somewhere. Let me search the file for any hex patterns that could be an appid.\n\nActually, there's another approach I haven't tried. Some wxapkg tools use the file's own data to determine the appid. Or I can try to extract appid-related data from the file header.\n\nWait, I know another approach! For WeChat Mini Programs, the appid is stored in the `project.config.json` of the development project. But since this is a compiled wxapkg (not source), the appid would be embedded in the encrypted content.\n\nHowever, there's another technique: some versions of wxapkg have the appid visible in the raw file at specific offsets. Let me scan the entire file for any wx-prefixed strings.\n\nActually, looking at the file, it starts with `V1MMWX` and then the rest is encrypted. But wait - there might be metadata before the encryption starts.\n\nLet me re-examine: the header is `V1MMWX` (6 bytes). After that, the next 4 bytes might be metadata like the data length. Let me look at the header structure more carefully.\n\nFor V1MMWX format:\n```\nBytes 0-5: Magic header \"V1MMWX\"\nBytes 6-9: Data length (32-bit LE)\nBytes 10-13: Name length (32-bit LE)\nBytes 14-...: Name (UTF-8)\nAfter name: Encrypted data\n```\n\nWait, let me re-check the file structure. Some versions store metadata in plaintext before the encrypted data.\n\nLet me examine offsets 6-20 more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_i8JkSEEoM04CBfu9hfX86239","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$script = @'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst pkg = fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw.wxapkg');\n\n// Read header structure\nconsole.log('Header:', pkg.slice(0, 6).toString());\n\n// After V1MMWX, try to read metadata fields\n// Try reading as LE/UInt32\nconst dataLen = pkg.readUInt32LE(6);\nconsole.log('Data length (LE at 6):', dataLen);\nconsole.log('Name length (LE at 10):', pkg.readUInt32LE(10));\n\n// Try as BE\nconsole.log('Data length (BE at 6):', pkg.readUInt32BE(6));\nconsole.log('Name length (BE at 10):', pkg.readUInt32BE(10));\n\n// Read potential name at offset 14\nconst nameLen = pkg.readUInt32LE(10);\nif (nameLen > 0 && nameLen < 200) {\n    const name = pkg.slice(14, 14 + nameLen).toString('utf8');\n    console.log('Name at 14:', name);\n}\n\n// Try another common format: offset 6 = name length, then name, then data\nconst possibleNameLen = pkg.readUInt32LE(6);\nconsole.log('\\nPossible name len:', possibleNameLen);\nif (possibleNameLen > 0 && possibleNameLen < 100) {\n    const possibleName = pkg.slice(10, 10 + possibleNameLen).toString('utf8');\n    console.log('Possible name:', possibleName);\n}\n\n// Look at first 100 bytes as hex\nconsole.log('\\nFirst 100 bytes hex:');\nfor (let i = 0; i < 100; i += 16) {\n    const hex = pkg.slice(i, i+16).toString('hex').match(/.{1,2}/g).join(' ');\n    const ascii = pkg.slice(i, i+16).toString('utf8').replace(/[^\\x20-\\x7E]/g, '.');\n    console.log(`${i.toString(16).padStart(4)}: ${hex.padEnd(48)} ${ascii}`);\n}\n\n// Try to find appid-like patterns by looking at EVERY possible offset\n// Search for 'wx' followed by 16 hex chars\nconsole.log('\\nSearching for wx-appid patterns in raw bytes...');\nlet found = 0;\nfor (let i = 6; i < pkg.length - 18; i++) {\n    const slice = pkg.slice(i, i + 18).toString('utf8');\n    if (/^wx[a-f0-9]{16}$/i.test(slice)) {\n        console.log(`Found at offset ${i}: ${slice}`);\n        found++;\n    }\n}\nif (found === 0) console.log('No wx appid pattern found in plaintext');\n\n// Try SHA256 + MD5 combo with every possible 18-byte prefix starting with 'wx'\n// Read the actual file and try to find the appid using \n// the assumption it might be in the metadata\nconsole.log('\\nTrying to read metadata section...');\n// V1MMWX + 4-byte unknown + remainder\nfor (let metaLen = 0; metaLen < 100; metaLen++) {\n    const meta = pkg.slice(6, 6 + metaLen).toString('utf8');\n    if (/^[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-\\/\\.]+$/.test(meta) && meta.length >= 10) {\n        console.log(`Potential metadata at 6+${metaLen}: \"${meta}\"`);\n    }\n}\n'@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"$env:TEMP\\analyze2.js\" -Value $script -Encoding utf8\nnode \"$env:TEMP\\analyze2.js\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":12853,"output":1282,"cacheRead":227328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":241463,"cost":{"input":0.0017994200000000001,"output":0.00035896,"cacheRead":0.006365183999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008523563999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096370738,"responseId":"5b10a065-c642-40d0-a5be-4107b3f63410"}}
