{"type":"message","id":"75c95fdf","parentId":"e61f8043","timestamp":"2026-06-10T13:00:50.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Network is not working. Let me try yet another approach - maybe I can decrypt the wxapkg using a different algorithm. There are known methods that work without the appid.\n\nActually, I just realized something important. The WeChat Mini Program wxapkg format has changed over time, and some newer tools can decrypt it using the `wxapkg` CLI tool that comes with WeChat dev tools, or by using the `encryptKey` from the dev tools' configuration.\n\nBut wait - there's another approach. The wxapkg file might be a subpackage rather than the main package. For `__APP__.wxapkg`, this is typically the main package. The appid might be derivable from the file's hash or embedded in the encrypted data in a known way.\n\nLet me try yet another decryption approach: some recent tools use the `pbkdf2` key derivation with specific parameters.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PB6pl443qwNk6gbN6XOL9895","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$script = @'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst crypto = require('crypto');\nconst zlib = require('zlib');\n\nconst pkg = fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw.wxapkg');\nconst encrypted = pkg.slice(6);\n\n// Try different V1MMWX decryption algorithms\n// These are from the open-source wxapkg-decompiler project\n\nconst approaches = [];\n\n// Approach: Generic V1 approach - try many common salts\nconst salts = ['', 'salt', 'salt2', 'salt1', 'encrypt', 'wx', 'mini', 'program',\n    'd24104997ed56929c0ab6ac4ffacb5f8',  // common salt from wxappUnpacker\n    '4d32e6d5703327aaf67ce1e3490e294c',\n    '00000000000000000000000000000000',\n];\n\nconst appids_guess = [\n    '', 'test', 'wxapp', 'miniprogram',\n    'wx09786c3fb9eac9a4',  // user miniprogram\n    'wxd506e81fe975a813',  // fox wechat\n];\n\n// Try all combinations of key derivation\nfor (const appid of ['wx09786c3fb9eac9a4', '', 'test', 'miniprogram', 'app']) {\n    for (const algo of [\n        // key=md5(appid+rand_salt), iv=md5(appid+rand_salt2)\n        (a) => {\n            const k = crypto.createHash('md5').update(a + 'd24104997ed56929c0ab6ac4ffacb5f8').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            const i = crypto.createHash('md5').update(a + '4d32e6d5703327aaf67ce1e3490e294c').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            return { key: k, iv: i, name: 'md5_salted' };\n        },\n        // Try without appid (just salts)\n        () => {\n            const k = crypto.createHash('md5').update('d24104997ed56929c0ab6ac4ffacb5f8').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            const i = crypto.createHash('md5').update('4d32e6d5703327aaf67ce1e3490e294c').digest().slice(0, 16);\n            return { key: k, iv: i, name: 'md5_salted_noappid' };\n        },\n        // key=sha256(appid)[0:16], iv=sha256(appid)[16:32]\n        (a) => {\n            const h = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(a).digest();\n            return { key: h.slice(0, 16), iv: h.slice(16, 32), name: 'sha256_split' };\n        },\n        // key=sha256(appid)[16:32], iv=sha256(appid)[0:16]\n        (a) => {\n            const h = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(a).digest();\n            return { key: h.slice(16, 32), iv: h.slice(0, 16), name: 'sha256_split_rev' };\n        },\n        // key=md5(appid), iv=md5(appid)\n        (a) => {\n            const h = crypto.createHash('md5').update(a).digest();\n            return { key: h, iv: h, name: 'md5_both' };\n        },\n        // PBKDF2\n        (a) => {\n            const k = crypto.pbkdf2Sync(a, 'salt', 1000, 32, 'sha256');\n            return { key: k.slice(0, 16), iv: k.slice(16, 32), name: 'pbkdf2' };\n        },\n        // sha256(a)[0:32], iv=zero\n        (a) => {\n            const k = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(a).digest();\n            return { key: k.slice(0, 16), iv: Buffer.alloc(16, 0), name: 'sha256_zerov' };\n        },\n        // sha256 \n        (a) => {\n            const h = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(a).digest();\n            return { key: h.slice(16, 32), iv: Buffer.alloc(16, 0), name: 'sha256_zerov2' };\n        },\n    ]) {\n        try {\n            const { key, iv } = algo(appid);\n            const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-cbc', key, iv);\n            let decrypted;\n            try {\n                decrypted = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(encrypted), decipher.final()]);\n            } catch(e) { continue; }\n            \n            // Try to decompress\n            try {\n                const decomp = zlib.inflateSync(decrypted.slice(0, decrypted.length));\n                const text = decomp.slice(0, 200).toString();\n                if (text.includes('.js') || text.includes('.json') || text.includes('App({') || text.includes('Page({')) {\n                    console.log(`✅ ${algo.name} with '${appid}': SUCCESS`);\n                    console.log(text.slice(0, 200));\n                    fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\zqw_decoded.wxapkg', decomp);\n                    process.exit(0);\n                }\n            } catch(e) {\n                // Check raw\n                const text = decrypted.slice(0, 200).toString();\n                if (text.includes('.js') || text.includes('.json') || text.includes('app.json') || text.match(/[\"\\'].+\\.(js|json|wxml)[\"\\']/)) {\n                    console.log(`✅ ${algo.name} with '${appid}' (raw): ${text.slice(0, 200)}`);\n                    process.exit(0);\n                }\n            }\n        } catch(e) {}\n    }\n}\n\n// LAST RESORT: Open the wxapkg with the WeChat dev tools' native module\n// Check if we can just use the dev tools directly\nconsole.log('All decryption approaches failed.');\nconsole.log('Need the correct appid for 涨棋网 mini program.');\n\n// Print what we can extract\nconsole.log('\\nFile info:');\nconsole.log('  Size: ~6MB');\nconsole.log('  Header: V1MMWX (v1 encrypted)');\nconsole.log('  Source: __APP__.wxapkg (main package)');\n'@\n\nSet-Content -Path \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt5.js\" -Value $script -Encoding utf8\nnode \"$env:TEMP\\decrypt5.js\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":85,"output":1772,"cacheRead":243968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":245825,"cost":{"input":0.000011900000000000001,"output":0.00049616,"cacheRead":0.006831104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0073391640000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096431351,"responseId":"e0ec915e-16ca-408f-8a59-a1fb7a4fa74d"}}
