{"type":"message","id":"92255909","parentId":"7db2ffa9","timestamp":"2026-06-10T13:01:00.696Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can't decrypt the wxapkg without knowing the appid. Let me try one more creative approach - maybe I can extract the appid from the WeChat dev tools by using its built-in wxapkg decryption capability.\n\nThe WeChat dev tools can open a project from a wxapkg (File → Open → Import). When it does this, it will decrypt the package using the correct appid. The appid might be available in the dev tools' logs or data.\n\nOr, let me check if there's a known tool that can extract appid from a wxapkg. Some tools analyze the encrypted data's statistical properties to determine the appid.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach: use the WeChat dev tools' command-line interface to try to open the package and see if it tells us the appid.\n\nWait, I just had another idea. Let me check if the file was downloaded using `miniprogram-downloader` or similar tools. The filename `APP---ff33cfef-ffc6-4195-95da-aaa0bba704ea.wxapkg` with the UUID-like pattern suggests it might have been downloaded from a specific source.\n\nAlso, there's a known technique: some tools save the appid in the file's modification time or in a sidecar file. Let me check if there's a companion file.\n\nActually, let me try the most practical approach now - since I can't decrypt the package without the appid, let me try to find the 涨棋网 mini program in the WeChat dev tools' recent project list.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_IzcPJDQc9xQiw8kQnaWQ9263","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check WeChat dev tools' recent projects and config files\n$devToolsPath = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\微信开发者工具\\User Data\\80d774828fc67c7dafc59cd74ce70db0\"\nGet-ChildItem $devToolsPath -Depth 1 -Filter \"*.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, Length\n\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Check for recent projects list\n$recentProjects = Get-ChildItem $devToolsPath -Recurse -Depth 4 -Filter \"recent*.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nforeach ($f in $recentProjects) {\n    Write-Host \"Found: $($f.FullName)\"\n    $content = Get-Content $f.FullName -Encoding UTF8 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue -TotalCount 20\n    Write-Host $content\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Check for any config that might list projects\nGet-ChildItem $devToolsPath -Recurse -Depth 4 -Include \"ide*.json\",\"global*.json\",\"projects*.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName, Length\n\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Also check the ff33cfef UUID in filenames\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\" -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"ff33cfef\" } | Select-Object FullName","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":131,"output":717,"cacheRead":245760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":246608,"cost":{"input":0.00001834,"output":0.00020076000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00688128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00710038}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781096450982,"responseId":"438bb30a-ef88-45c2-8c7b-fa810d399e41"}}
