{"type":"message","id":"2a415301","parentId":"312b6fb7","timestamp":"2026-06-10T13:11:42.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `-SkipCertificateCheck` parameter isn't available in this version of PowerShell. Let me try without it, and with auth token.\n\nActually, the GitLab server uses SSH, so it's probably self-hosted and may not have the API accessible without proper token. Let me try to use the git command to test access.\n\nActually, a simpler approach would be to use `git` itself to check if the user has access. I can check by trying to fetch from the repo using the user's credentials, or by looking at the `.git/config` for any access control lists.\n\nBut wait - this is a GitLab server and the user wants to know if \"摇摇晃晃(李胜飞)\" has git permissions to the main repo (nightoffullmoon) and its submodules. The most reliable way to check is via GitLab's API or web interface.\n\nLet me try another approach - see if there's a gitlab personal access token saved somewhere, or if I can generate one.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Ctk7Qs3RtJAspZcl78sP9241","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to access GitLab with basic auth\nWrite-Host \"=== GitLab API check ===\"\n# Check if the git remote SSH key is set up and can authenticate\ncd E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\n\nWrite-Host \"=== Check current user ===\"\ngit config user.name\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Check if lishengfei has access via SSH ===\"\n# Try SSH connection to gitlab\nssh -T git@git.devcloud.ztgame.com 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5\n\n# Check if there's a key for lishengfei\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== SSH keys loaded ===\"\nssh-add -l 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":193,"output":420,"cacheRead":252416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":253029,"cost":{"input":0.000027020000000000002,"output":0.00011760000000000001,"cacheRead