{"type":"message","id":"d22ab553","parentId":"a08899d1","timestamp":"2026-06-10T13:11:54.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the current SSH key is for `@yyzypublic`. I'm logged in as `yyzypublic`. This is the user's own GitLab account, not lishengfei's.\n\nTo check lishengfei's permissions, I need to use the GitLab API. Since the SSH authentication works for `@yyzypublic`, I might be able to use the GitLab API with the HTTP credentials.\n\nLet me check if there's a GitLab personal access token or session cookie stored somewhere. The GitLab API needs authentication to view project members.\n\nLet me try to find the API access by looking at common GitLab credential stores.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6u0pPBee7xDPdfdoOVWI8110","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Look for GitLab personal access tokens\nWrite-Host \"=== Check for .git-credentials ===\"\nGet-Content \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.git-credentials\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_ -match \"devcloud\" }\n\nWrite-Host \"=== Check Windows Credential Manager ===\"\ncmdkey /list 2>&1 | findstr \"devcloud git\"\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Try to get a GitLab API token ===\"\n# The SSH session works. Let me try to access GitLab API over HTTPS\n# Try with git http.extraHeader\ncd E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\n\n# Check if we can do git ls-remote (this requires auth)\nWrite-Host \"=== Git ls-remote test (lishengfei) ===\"\n# We can't impersonate lishengfei, but we can check what permissions a specific user has if we have admin access\n\n# Let me try the GitLab API with the existing workhorse token or session\n# Check common API token locations\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\GitLab\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:APPDATA\\GitLab\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name\n\n# Try to find any token file\nGet-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\.git\" -Recurse -Filter \"*token*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name\nGet-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\.git\" -Recurse -Filter \"*credential*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Try curl for GitLab API with SSH key auth ===\"\n# The GitLab API might accept the SSH key for auth if we use the right endpoint\ntry {\n    $result = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/user\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 10\n    if ($result.StatusCode -eq 200) {\n        Write-Host \"Got user info!\"\n        $result.Content | ConvertFrom-Json | Select-Object id, username, name, email\n    }\n} catch {\n    $statusCode = $_.Exception.Response.StatusCode.value__ 2>$null\n    Write-Host \"API returned: $statusCode\"\n}\n\n# Try to use the gitlab-ci-token\nif ($env:CI_JOB_TOKEN) {\n    Write-Host \"CI JOB TOKEN found!\"\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":257,"output":753,"cacheRead":252928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":253938,"cost":{"input":0.000035980000000000004,"output":0.00021084,"cacheRead":0.0070819839999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0073288039999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781097103614,"responseId":"c8a54743-25a0-4e67-9910-d35122676461"}}
