{"type":"message","id":"0110861a","parentId":"d599f375","timestamp":"2026-06-10T13:33:43.564Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can't download HttpCanary directly because GitHub and other sites are blocked/not accessible. The emulator might be able to access it though since it uses a different network (10.0.2.x NAT). Let me try to download it via the emulator using `curl` or `wget`.\n\nActually, since the emulator is Android 12 and rooted, I can use `curl` inside the emulator to download the APK, then pull it to the host.\n\nBut first, let me check if curl is available on the emulator.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YQ6Y0lDLtiCSbXrSdDMk5208","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$adb = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\PlaybackEngines\\AndroidPlayer\\SDK\\platform-tools\\adb.exe\"\n\n# Check if curl or wget is available in the emulator\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"which curl\" 2>&1\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"which wget\" 2>&1\n\n# Try to download via emulator's network (uses NAT, might have different routing)\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Trying emulator download ===\"\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"su -c 'curl -L -o /sdcard/HttpCanary.apk https://github.com/MegatronKing/HttpCanary/releases/latest/download/HttpCanary.apk'\" 2>&1\n\n# Check if download succeeded\nStart-Sleep 10\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 shell \"ls -la /sdcard/HttpCanary.apk\" 2>&1\n\n# If it worked, pull it\n& $adb -s 127.0.0.1:7555 pull /sdcard/HttpCanary.apk \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\HttpCanary.apk\" 2>&1","timeout":60,"yieldMs":20000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":381,"output":511,"cacheRead":268032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":268924,"cost":{"input":0.00005334,"output":0.00014308000000000002,"cacheRead":0.007504896,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007701316}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp"